code_changes.content:
{
  "buggy_files": [
    "drivers/platform/x86/acer-wmi.c"
  ],
  "buggy_functions": [
    "video_vendor_dmi_table"
  ],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Acer TravelMate 5735Z laptop is missing from the video_vendor_dmi_table DMI quirks list in acer-wmi.c. This causes the acer-wmi driver to incorrectly try to control backlight brightness on this specific model, which fails. The hardware actually requires the ACPI video driver's native backlight interface to work correctly (verified by the bug reporter who confirmed it works with 'acpi_backlight=native'). The fix is to add a DMI entry for TravelMate 5735Z to the video_vendor_dmi_table with the video_set_backlight_video_vendor callback, which will disable acer-wmi's brightness capability and allow the generic ACPI video driver to handle backlight control instead."
}

